title: Amazing place, but go there early morning
text: This is amazing, majestic place, huge piece of history, wonderful views. Be sure you head there early morning if you want to take nice photos and see the place without the crowd. 1-2 hours after opening the place is packed with people

title: Amazing place
text: Must-see if you are in Kalbarri, beautiful gorge and rock formations. All trails around the Z Bend are worth walking
place: The Loop and Z Bend Gorge

title: Amazing rock but bit overcrowded
text: It is really amazing rock formation, definitely must-see if you are in the area. As all the people want to take a picture inside the window it may get very overcrowded. There is also 9km trail starting at Nature’s Window - one of the best trails I’ve ever done

title: Definitely worth visit
text: This is great spot to visit if you are in Kalbarri. Needs proper light to be really pink though, otherwise it looks more greyish

title: Great fish and chips
text: Great fish&chips place. Fish fresh and tasty and chips not too oily. We visit The Jetty Shack every time we come to Kalbarri

title: Wonderful trail
text: This is short but amazing walk trail, especially when you walk among the rocks few meters from the ocean! One of the most beautiful places around!!!

title: Amazing rocks formation
text: I was very impressed with that place, amazing cliffs not far from Perth. Looks stunning especially in the arvo when the sun is right. Definitely will be coming back when I am around

title: Beautiful spot
text: Nice hidden spot in the WA South West. You can get there walking (Cape to Cape trail) or driving (4WD only). Definitely worth checking out. Waterfall by itself is not too high but looks very interesting, some kind of small jungle-type oasis among dunes.

title: Amazing location
text: Great beach about 3-4 hours drive from Perth. Amazing location and awesome views. Bit hard to swim due to massive waves, enjoyed the stay though

title: Driver service
text: We used this company to provide us with whole-day driver+car service (2 days in a row). Our driver Eka was very professional, always on time and always happy to help. We did couple of really long trips to remote locations and everything was great. Can definitely recommend it

title: Amazing waterfalls, but don’t get ripped off
text:
Both waterfalls (Sekumpul and Fiji) are amazing, beautfiul location, true gems in Bali. But... on our way we passed at least 4-5 „Registration Point” which basically want to take the money for „access to waterfall” - just pass them, don’t talk to them. At the car park another guys want to rip you off, saying that you need to hire a guide as the road is dangerous and complicated (which cost around $30k per person) - bulls**it, just walk down the trail for about 1 km and you will see real ticket booth ($2k per person). Trail is not hard you can do both waterfalls within 2 hours (took as slight longer as we had a lunch at Sekumpul Restaurant) - you don’t need any guide!!! And there is no obligation to hire any (even if they tell you something else). I don’t mind paying people for the services they offer, but cannot stand lies and ripoffs.
Trail as itself is beautiful, fantastic experience. Waterfalls are majestic (especially if you come relatively early, before midday as you can avoid crowd). Amazing jungle location

title: Great place
text: Great to see monkeys around (and on yourself too). Beautiful scenery, deifinitely worth the price we had to pay ($50k per person),

title: Great place, great service, location is the problem
text: This is amazing place, clean and nice stay with awesome staff. The only problem is location, far from Ubud and considering there are not too many pavements around it is really hard to get there (unless you will gat a „rip off taxi” - they quoted us 200k IDR for a 3km trip from Ubud to Ila Villa...)

title: Nice and relaxing walk
text: Nice and relaxing walk, great views at the beginning of the trail, once you get to all the shops/cafes/restaurants it loses its mood. Easy 3-4km return (unless you’re going to go to the end of it)

title: Beautiful place
text: This cave is the most beautiful caves in Margaret River region. Lovely location, and amazing rock forms (including impressing suspended table). Bit expensive though for such a small cave

title: Just the lookout
text: Nice drive up to the hill. Lookout by itself is very average, no spectacular views around, just the hill

title: Interesting place if its on your way
text: MR sculpture park is very interesting place to see, weird looking figures definitely catch the eye. Wouldn’t do that as a main attraction in the region but definitely worth seeing if you are in the area.

title: Beautiful Park
text: This is definitely one of the most beautiful parks I’ve ever visited. Wonderful beaches surrounded by trees and rocks, great 4WD tracks and nice Frenchman Peak trail. Definitely must see if you are around

title: Wonderful trail
text: This is short but amazing walk trail, especially when you walk among the rocks few meters from the ocean! One of the most beutiful places around!!!

title: Nice spot
text: Red Bluff is nice spot with some amazing views. Lots of people though so it is busy and noisy usual (been there 3 times and each time there were plenty of people over there). Very short walk and easy access so basically anyone can go there. Short drive from Kalbarri centre

title: Great campsite
text: Great campsite with plenty if space. clean amenities and cosy beach just around the corner. We stayed there in Feb - great sunny weather and not too many flies (they showed up only in the mornings). Great base to travel around (Walpole-Nornalup NP, William Bay NP etc.)

title: Nice walk but expensive too
text:
Bit too expensive for what you get. Not worth $21 (just for 600m of walk). Ancient Tree walk in the bottom of the forrest offers more for free
Not saying it's not interesting because it is, just slight overpriced so won't do that again when I'm around

title: Amazing walk
text: This is absolutely must-see if you are in area. Short but amazing walk among massive trees with Giant Tingle at the end (which is outstanding).

title: Amazing Park
text: Great park to a few-days visit, not as crowdy as Cape Le Grand (around 200km East) what is massive advantage. Nice walking trails and beaches, beautiful flora (haven't seen some of the flowers anywhere else), and great 4WD tracks. Definitely will be coming back

title: Best Chinese in Perth
text: So far it's been the best Chinese restaurant in Perth, food tasty and fresh, great service. I'm not huge fan of Asian food byt I enjoyed it at Joy Kitchen

title: Great spot, amazing views and awesome beach
text: It's a bit of drive from Carnarvon but definitely worth it. Amazing views (especially during the sunset) and awesome beach about 1km South.

title: Very stirring place, lots of cool exhibits
text: Didn't expect such a nice museum before I headed there. Plenty of amazing exhibits and stories about the space programs. Very helpful and knowledgable staff. If you are in Carnarvon that's a must-see place

title: Better than Busselton Jetty
text: One Mile Jetty is not as long as Busselton one but definitely it was much better experience. Bit sluttish but it adds the charm. Not many people around which is an advantage.

title: Amazing looking beach but too busy and too windy
text: Turquoise Bay looks amazing but there are definitely too many people usually so if you don't like busy places that's not great destination. Reef is very close to the beach so you can dive even if you are not good swimmer. There was massive wind when we were there so it was bit cold.

title: Great ocean views
text: Definitely worth checking if you are in the area. Amazing ocean views. Bit busy but except that it's very cosy place with some good stories to read

title: Great rock but nothing else around
text: it is an amazing shaped rock but in my opinion it's not worth driving 4 hours one way (there is almost nothing else around, short walk on Wave Rock and Mulka Cave 20km from there). Definitely worth checking if it's on your way somewhere.

title: If you are at Wave Rock definitely go and see Hippo's Yawn
text: Nice rock short walk from Wave Rock. Plenty of flies on the way through the woods. Worth checking if you have a while over there.

title: Stunning Aboriginal painting inside
text: If you are at Wave Rock you should definitely drive to Mulka Cave too. Cave is not massive but there are plenty of Aboriginal paintings inside. Lots of flies around

title: Amazing 4x4 road, stunning views
text: One of my favourite places in Exmouth area. Stunning 4x4 road to the canyon - road unsealed, plenty of rocks so may be risky going there with the standard 2WD or AWD with low clearance. Beautiful place, will be definitely coming back when I'm in this area again

title: Nick wreck you can see close from the coast
text: I went there on my way to the Yardie Creek but it was definitely worth checking out. You can clearly see the wreck as it is not too far from the coast. Great spot for a sunset.

title: Outstanding place
text: One of the most beautiful places I've ever seen! Must see if you are in area. Amazing rocks and awesome trails. Go to the bottom of the gorge, trail is spectacular
place: The Loop and Z Bend Gorge

title: Amazing place
text: Amazing views! You can feel power of the ocean when the waves hit the rocks. One of the most outstanding places I've ever seen

title: Great ride
text: Very comfortable route. Amazing views all the time, very small traffic (even during the christmas period). Pure pleasure of driving

title: Fantastic cave
text: It was great to see this cave, not too big but amazing inside. I've seen many caves in Europe before but this one is the cosiest.

title: Nice place with very tasty beer
text: Little Creatures is a very nice restaurant with tasty beer selection. Food is not bad too. Little bit pricy but all restaurants in Fremantle are like that.

title: Nice trails and BBQ area
text: Ghost Walk Trail (9.5km) is easy and nice trail for Sunday afternoon. And there are plenty of BBQ's so you can relax after walking. Place is nice but nit amazing

title: Awesome building
text: I've been really impressed with engineer job they made to build such a complicated building. Looks awesome and all locations around are great as well

title: Great place in the centre of Perth
text: Kings Park is great place to take some rest and just relax. Plenty of walking routes and amazing city views. All in one!

title: Nice beach with amazing rocks.
text: What I like about this beach - there were not too many people when I visited it so I could just relax without shouting people around me.
